'''B-25轰炸机撞击帝国大厦事故'''是一起发生于1945年的[[航空事故|航空事故]]，[[美國陸軍航空軍|美國陸軍航空軍]]一架[[B-25米切尔型轰炸机|B-25米切尔型轰炸机]]在浓雾中飞行时撞上了当时世界最高的[[摩天大樓|摩天大楼]][[帝国大厦|帝国大厦]]。事故并未破坏帝国大厦的建筑结构完整性，但造成14人遇难，遇难者中包括全部3名机组成员和建筑内的11人。事故还造成了约1,000,000美元（折合当前{{formatnum:{{Inflation|US|1000000|1945|r=-6}}}}美元）的经济损失。<ref>{{cite web |url=http://history1900s.about.com/od/1940s/a/empirecrash.htm |title=The Plane That Crashed Into the Empire State Building |author=Jennifer Rosenberg |publisher=about.com |accessdate=2014-05-03 |archive-date=2017-03-04 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170304033843/http://history1900s.about.com/od/1940s/a/empirecrash.htm |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name=JOM>{{cite web |url=http://www.tms.org/pubs/journals/JOM/0112/News/News8-0112.html |title=Empire State Building Withstood Airplane Impact |publisher=JOM (monthly publication of The Minerals, Metals & Materials Society) |date=2001 |accessdate=2014-05-03 |archive-date=2014-08-08 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140808145606/http://www.tms.org/pubs/journals/JOM/0112/News/News8-0112.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>

==事故经过==
[[File:North_American_Aviation's_B-25_medium_bomber,_Inglewood,_Calif.jpg|thumb]]]]
事故发生于1945年7月28日周六，美國陸軍航空軍中校小威廉·富兰克林·史密斯（{{lang|en|William Franklin Smith, Jr.}}）驾驶一架[[B-25米切尔型轰炸机|B-25米切尔型轰炸机]]执行常规的人员转移任务。飞机从[[马萨诸塞州|马萨诸塞州]]的{{link-en|汉斯科姆空军基地|Hanscom Air Force Base|漢斯科姆飛行場}}起飞，飞往[[拉瓜地亞機場|拉瓜地亞機場]]。<ref name="history">{{cite web|url=http://www.history.com/this-day-in-history/plane-crashes-into-empire-state-building|title=Plane crashes into Empire State Building|work=History.com|accessdate=2014-05-03|archive-date=2014-03-25|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140325152018/http://www.history.com/this-day-in-history/plane-crashes-into-empire-state-building|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|last=Berman|first=John S.|title=The Empire State Building: The Museum of the City of New York|year=2003|publisher=Barnes,John & Noble Publishing|url=http://books.google.com/books?id=MDotCyoCdn8C&pg=PA85&dq|access-date=2014-05-03|archive-date=2013-11-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131126203353/http://books.google.com/books?id=MDotCyoCdn8C&pg=PA85&dq|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Barron|first=James|title=Flaming Horror on the 79th Floor; 50 Years Ago Today, in the Fog, a Plane Hit the World's Tallest Building|url=http://www.nytimes.com/1995/07/28/nyregion/flaming-horror-79th-floor-50-years-ago-today-fog-plane-hit-world-s-tallest.html|accessdate=2012-11-17|newspaper=The New York Times|date=1995-07-28|archive-date=2013-06-17|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130617231911/http://www.nytimes.com/1995/07/28/nyregion/flaming-horror-79th-floor-50-years-ago-today-fog-plane-hit-world-s-tallest.html|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|last=Byers|first=Roland O.|title=Flak dodger: a story of the 457th Bombardment Group, 1943-1945, 8th AAF|year=1985|publisher=Pawpaw Press}}</ref>当天天气有雾，而飞机进入纽约上空时，天气状况变得更糟。史密斯联系了拉瓜地亞機場请求降落许可，然而机场塔台告知他当时能见度为零，建议他不要降落，<ref name="npr">{{cite web |url=http://www.npr.org/templates/story/story.php?storyId=92987873 |title=The Day A Bomber Hit The Empire State Building |author=Joe Richman |publisher=[[NPR|NPR]] |date=2008-07-28 |accessdate=2014-05-03 |archive-date=2014-06-05 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140605073019/http://www.npr.org/templates/story/story.php?storyId=92987873 |dead-url=no }}</ref>并指示他转而降落到[[纽瓦克机场|纽瓦克机场]]。<ref name="history"/>但飞行员却执意继续飞行，在大雾中迷失了方向。<ref name="guinness" />他于是保持在较低的高度飞行，飞行速度也较慢，试图看清前方的飞行路线。<ref name="history"/>然而史密斯在飞行中却犯下了致命错误，误认为自己在[[曼哈顿|曼哈顿]]西部上空，<ref name="guinness" />而在避开[[克莱斯勒大厦|克莱斯勒大厦]]后，飞机本应左转，但他却误向右转，这一失误使飞机径直向[[帝国大厦|帝国大厦]]飞去。<ref name="history"/><ref name="guinness" />

[[File:Empire_State_Building_from_the_Top_of_the_Rock.jpg|thumb]]
[[UTC-4|当地时间]]早上9:40，飞机撞上了帝国大厦北侧78层和80层之间，在大厦外墙撞出了一个{{convert|18|ft|m}}×{{convert|20|ft|m}}的洞，机上的燃油引发了爆炸。飞机残骸中的燃油沿大厦外墙倾泻而下，引发了大火。火焰蔓延到大厦的75层，整座大厦都“变成了火把”。<ref name="history"/><ref name="VOA">{{cite web|url=http://blogs.voanews.com/tedlandphairsamerica/2012/05/04/the-empire-state-building-no-2-in-new-york-1-in-our-hearts/|title=The Empire State Building: No. 2 in New York, 1 in Our Hearts|work=[[VOA|VOA]]|date=2012-05-04|accessdate=2014-05-03|archive-date=2014-05-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140503191335/http://blogs.voanews.com/tedlandphairsamerica/2012/05/04/the-empire-state-building-no-2-in-new-york-1-in-our-hearts/|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="On This Day in Aviation History: July 28th" />一个引擎击穿了大楼，从撞击点对面的大楼南侧飞出，飞过一个街区后落在{{convert|900|ft|m}}外的一栋临近建筑的屋顶上，引发的火灾烧毁了一间阁楼。另一个引擎和起落架的部分残骸落入了电梯井中。事故引发了大火，上百名消防员被派遣到高处灭火，在当时成为纽约消防史上楼层最高的灭火任务，这一纪录直至2001年[[九一一袭击事件|九一一袭击事件]]才被打破。大火持续燃烧了40分钟后被扑灭，而这也是人类历史上首次控制住这一高度的{{link-en|高层建筑火灾|Skyscraper fire}}。<ref name="On This Day in Aviation History: July 28th">{{cite web|url=http://nycaviation.com/2009/07/28/on-this-day-in-aviation-history-july-28th/|title=On This Day in Aviation History: July 28th|last=Molnar|first=Matt|publisher=NYCAviation|accessdate=2009-07-28|archive-date=2009-08-01|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090801112745/http://nycaviation.com/2009/07/28/on-this-day-in-aviation-history-july-28th/|dead-url=no}}</ref>大火扑灭后，整栋大厦依然保持完好，只有飞机残骸仍然卡在建筑中。<ref name="VOA"/>

事故共造成14人遇难。其中包括机上的飞行员史密斯与另外全部两名机组人员：克里斯托弗·多米特洛维奇（{{lang|en|Christopher Domitrovich}}）[[上士|上士]]和搭乘飞机的航空機械士艾伯特·佩尔纳（{{lang|en|Albert Perna}}）。佩尔纳的遗体沿电梯井落入了建筑底部，事故两天后才被搜救人员发现。<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.aerospaceweb.org/question/history/q0311.shtml |title=B-25 Empire State Building Collision |publisher=Aerospaceweb.org |accessdate=2012-04-08 |archive-date=2009-07-06 |archive-url=http://arquivo.pt/wayback/20090706192155/http://www.aerospaceweb.org/question/history/q0311.shtml |dead-url=no }}</ref>另外建筑物内也有11人遇难，这11人当时都在直接受到飞机撞击的{{link-en|战争救济服务社|Catholic Relief Services}}和{{link-en|国家天主教福利委员会|National Catholic Welfare Council}}办公室。<ref name="history"/><ref name=JOM/>大厦内的[[電梯小姐|电梯操作员]]贝蒂·露·奥利弗（{{lang|en|Betty Lou Oliver}}）在事故中受伤后，搜救人员本想用电梯将她转移至安全地带，不料电梯缆绳已在事故中严重受损，轿厢下坠了75层，但电梯中的奥利弗却得以幸存。她也因此成为[[吉尼斯世界纪录大全|-{zh-cn:吉尼斯世界纪录;zh-tw:金氏世界紀錄;zh-hk:健力士世界紀錄;zh-sg:健力士世界纪录;}-]]中在电梯事故中下坠距离最长的幸存者。<ref name="guinness">{{cite web |url=http://www.guinnessworldrecords.com/content_pages/record.asp?recordid=53746 |title=Longest Fall Survived In An Elevator |publisher=guinnessworldrecords.com |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20060317041607/http://www.guinnessworldrecords.com/content_pages/record.asp?recordid=53746 |archivedate=2006-03-17 |accessdate=2014-05-03 }}</ref> 
